4808 
4809   // (X >  Y) ? X : max(X, Y) --> max(X, Y)
4810   // (X >= Y) ? X : max(X, Y) --> max(X, Y)
4811   // (X <  Y) ? X : min(X, Y) --> min(X, Y)
4812   // (X <= Y) ? X : min(X, Y) --> min(X, Y)
4813   //
4814   // The equivalence allows a vector select (shuffle) of max/min and Y. Ex:
4815   // (X > Y) ? X : (Z ? max(X, Y) : Y)
4816   // If Z is true, this reduces as above, and if Z is false:
4817   // (X > Y) ? X : Y --> max(X, Y)
4818   ICmpInst::Predicate MMPred = MMI->getPredicate();
