4401 // The value is only poison, if any of these values are poison.
4402 // It can be useful to decide if replacing a value with another would be
4403 // refining or introduce more poison.
4404 //
4405 // It is especially useful for select instructions. When it comes to selects and
4406 // impliesPoison, if select is the ValueAssumedToBePoison it is rare that it
4407 // yields true for any Value, that isn't a user of the select, due to the fact
4408 // that a select has more complex poison propagation than other instruction.
4409 static bool areTheseAllTheValuesThatMayCausePoisonInValue(
4410     const SmallVector<const Value *, 2> ValuesAssumedPoison, const Value *V,
4411     unsigned Depth) {
4412   if (any_of(ValuesAssumedPoison, [V](const auto *P) { return P == V; }))
